## Public Member Functions

### next() {#acb5c8bd7367e9f8df487f08bdd08bc27}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; Remark &gt; &gt; YAMLRemarkParser::next ()</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
If no error occurs, this returns a valid <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/remarks/remark">Remark</a> object.

If an error of type <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/remarks/endoffileerror">EndOfFileError</a> occurs, it is safe to recover from it by stopping the parsing. If any other error occurs, it should be propagated to the user. The pointer should never be null.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/remarks/yamlremarkparser-h/#l00066">66</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/remarks/yamlremarkparser-h">YAMLRemarkParser.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/remarks/yamlremarkparser-cpp/#l00416">416</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/remarks/yamlremarkparser-cpp">YAMLRemarkParser.cpp</a>.
